text: I think people missed the point of this movie. It's not just about a stupid mirror killing shits, in my opinion - it's about those 2 children who were traumatized by the event that they made up the whole story to help them cope with it. Just like the guy says - he got help, while his sis was all alone. They made him well in the mental institution, but as doctor has told him, what's more important than to connect w\ his sister is his recovery. And having mental problems herself, she made her little brother relapse. And because of that, he blames it all on the mirror. Though as he said it himself - the mirror is old, and chances are his sister looked through a pile of cases, to find few ones that fit the story they made up, to help help them deal w\ it. It's all in their mind.

text: I'm a huge horror fan. Many movies make me think "Ok, that was a pretty good horror movie". I hate jumpscares, and I like it when you, the viewer, is dragged in and feel unsafe yourself. Honestly, Oculus is one of the scariest movies I've ever seen. To put it simple: It fucked with my mind. So hard. I loved it. It just made me feel confused at first, but things made more and more sense as the movie progressed. The way it was filmed was very unique and awesome. And at the few points a jumpscare actually happened, they worked. It scared the living shit out of me. I can't say this about many other movie, but I was actually afraid of sleeping after watching this. Great movie.
